"if someone sends you a link, open it" is terrible advice, especially coming from a trusted source like Stanford.

Sure, technically speaking the Bill Nye post ticks the box for "framing as a debate" however it appears to be a blurb from an article that supports action in climate change and "framing as a debate" is a manipulative technique that really only applies to climate change denial. In context, the only really questionable aspect for pro-climate change rhetoric in that article is that they frame Bill Nye as an expert and he is not even kind of an expert in climate change. He's barely a scientist at all, much as I love him.
